pullRequest.title: Implementation of a trie data structure for residents, towns, and nations
pullRequest.bodyText:
Description:

Thanks to @suneettipirneni for suggesting using a trie
This pull request adds a trie structure which is built asynchronously upon the loading of Towny. It makes searching through many residents, towns, and nations for tab complete suggestions nearly instant. One test was conducted with 20,000 nations, and fetching completions with one character, for example typing "a", took 7ms. Fetching with two characters or more is nearly instant (>1ms).
Changes include:

Added Trie.java
Added residentsTrie, townsTrie, and nationsTrie to TownyUniverse
All tries are built asynchronously when TownyUniverse is loaded
New methods in BaseCommand.java:
getTownyStartingWith() and filterByStartOrGetTownyStartingWith()
Removal of unnecessary methods in NameUtil.java
Removal of MAX_RETURNS because the only usage is with possible subcommands (e.g. nationTabCompletes), not residents, towns, or nations which could return hundreds of results



 I have tested this pull request for defects on a server.
